We are seeking a Growth Marketing Manager to join our NYC team in a full-time role. This position is intended for college graduates with at least 1 year of proven experience with a solid foundation in growth marketing, as detailed below.


You will work alongside our marketing team to strategize and execute on a range of growth marketing campaigns that disruptive brands leverage to grow exponentially and will also gain exposure to the startup scene in New York. The role will foster you to grow a data-driven approach to implementing, optimizing, and analyzing campaigns across digital marketing channels.


**Quick Facts**


* Location: NYC
* Hours: Full-time
* Compensation: $70,000 base salary per year with comprehensive benefits (health insurance, 401k, travel allowance)
* Working Model: Hybrid (days are flexible, but in-office work is expected at least once per week)
* Start Date: TBD

**About Us**


* Superbolt is an award winning, direct-to-consumer agency that specializes in unlocking long-term growth for brands that matter. We're a multidisciplinary team of growth experts, data strategists, and creatives—all under one roof.
* Our clients' work spans across industries, from eco-friendly consumer products to modern healthcare solutions. We collaborate closely with our clients as a full-service, transparent extension of their in-house teams—to drive awareness, growth, and customer retention.
* We deliver for our clients by fostering team members who love working together, who are empowered to contribute fresh ideas that push us forward. If this sounds interesting to you, we're growing fast—and we'd love to meet you.


**What You'll Do**


* Customer Acquisition including paid social, paid search, display, partnerships, out-of-home;
* Website optimization including A/B testing, email collection, landing page customization;
* Lifecycle marketing including email marketing, referral programs, loyalty programs;
* Build multi-channel marketing strategies to drive incremental results that directly impact the top line of clients' businesses;
* Implement digital marketing campaigns on paid social channels (e.g. Facebook, Instagram, Pinterest, Twitter, Snapchat), direct response channels and email marketing campaigns;
* Analyze and extract meaningful marketing insights from various channels and analytics platforms;
* Create and deliver presentations of test results and strategies to clients.


**Who You Are**


* Bachelor's degree in an analytical field or related field;
* At least 1 year of proven growth marketing experience (including but not limited to hands-on experience managing and optimizing paid channels on behalf of clients such as on Meta Ads Platform, Google Ads Platform, and TikTok Ads Platform, as well as work experience with Google Analytics and Shopify);
* Solid track record of inspiring action based on data-driven insights;
* Able to work efficiently under tight deadlines and manage multiple priorities simultaneously;
* Proven ability to clearly communicate complex concepts to non-technical audiences;
* Confidently able to maneuver between working cooperatively in a team-oriented and cross-functional environment, as well as independently;
* Experience at a fast growing-startup is a plus;
* People management experience a plus but not required;
* Legally authorized to work in the United States. We are currently not sponsoring work visas to candidates.


**Interview Process**


* Round 1: A video interview with our operations team to learn more about your background and career interests.
* Round 2: A live case study and video interview with a senior member of the marketing team.
* Round 3: A take-home case study and follow up interview with senior members of the marketing team.


**Perks**


* Competitive salary
* Health insurance (medical, dental, vision)
* 401k retirement with a match
* Generous vacation days
* Transportation reimbursement
* Weekly happy hours
* Regular company events
* A great team and office in downtown Manhattan!


Superbolt is an Equal Opportunity Employer - without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status.


No recruiters please!
